Field Detail

mPccMsgHandler

public Messenger mPccMsgHandler
Handles cmd msgs coming from pcc Having one handler for all the devices allows us to catch global events and decreases resource usage. Furthermore, since the Ant chip can only take one cmd at a time, we aren't bottlenecking the cmd pipeline

dumbfireSendResult

public void dumbfireSendResult(Messenger msgr,
                               Message reply)
Sends the reply message to the messenger. This function swallows the RemoteException so it should only be used as a convenience function on final replies before exiting processing.
